Epigyne (Fig. 21
D-F
): dark, posterior margin truncated and straight (Fig. 21D). Scape strongly squared, wide and short (Fig. 21
E-F
). Copulatory openings near the posterior margin of the epigyne, separated from each other by about two times the spermathecal diameters (Fig. 21
D-E
). Spermathecae small and ovoid, separated from each other by about two diameters (Fig. 21F). Fertilization ducts thin and long, reaching the spermathecae with 3.5 coils (Fig. 21F). Copulatory ducts thick and short, swollen and nearly straight (Fig. 21E).
